import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['u'], data['v'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('u')
    ax.set_ylabel('v')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between u and v?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.heatmap(data, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt='.2f', linewidths=.05)

    return plt

chart = plot(data[['u', 'v']])
